First, we need to find the Cartesian product AxB. AxB is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a is in A and b is in B.

AxB = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4)}

Now, we need to find the union of (AxB) and C. The union of two sets is the set of all elements that are in either set.

C = {(1,3), (2,4)}

(AxB) U C = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4)}

So, (AxB) U C = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4)}.
